# Purpose

Enable the **Forge lifecycle MCP portfolio** on a product project scaffolded from the bootstrap toolkit, without vendoring Forge server code into the product repository.

Validated integration patterns come from the Project-1 harness (`nicksinx` Forge repos + OKF operator layer). Full policy detail lives in the bootstrap repo lessons: `.okf/improvements/forge-lifecycle-bootstrap-lessons.md` (bootstrap kit) and per-server repos.

# Architecture

```text
Sibling clones (../ConceptForge, ../LaunchForge, …)
        ↑
Product project (this repo)
  scripts/*-mcp.sh     → resolve sibling paths, pin versions
  .cursor/mcp.json     → Cursor MCP launchers (gitignored)
  .okf/forge/*         → per-server workspaces (gitignored)
  .okf/                → curated memory (promotion target)
```

**Option C integration:** OKF is the substrate; Forge owns lifecycle computation and signed packets; promotion to OKF is one-way and review-gated. See `.okf/decisions/0002-okf-forge-integration.md`.

Forge is **not** a sixth OKF bootstrap service. Enable Forge **after** the five-service OKF setup (Cursor → Codex → Claude → Xcode → Perplexity).

# Setup order

1. Complete OKF bootstrap validation: `scripts/okf-validate`, `scripts/validate_launch.sh`.
2. Clone Forge siblings (optional helper): `scripts/forge-clone-siblings.sh` or manual clones as peers of this project.
3. Build each Forge repo: `cd ../<Repo> && npm ci && npm run build`.
4. Copy MCP config: `cp .cursor/mcp-forge-lifecycle.json.example .cursor/mcp.json`.
5. Reload Cursor MCP; confirm launchers resolve sibling `dist/index.js` (LaunchForge uses `mcp-server/dist/index.js`).
6. Run server smokes in sibling repos before relying on cross-MCP handoffs.

# Launcher conventions

| Pattern | Rationale |
|---------|-----------|
| Bash launcher in `scripts/<server>-mcp.sh` | Avoids `${env:VAR}` limitations in `.cursor/mcp.json` |
| `*_ROOT` defaults to `../<Repo>` | Sibling layout keeps product repo clean |
| `*_WORKSPACE` under `.okf/forge/<stage>/` | Gitignored runtime state, not OKF concepts |
| Version pin via `*_MIN_VERSION` env | Fail fast when sibling checkout drifts |
| `assert-contracts-version.mjs` when present | Shared `@forge-lifecycle/contracts` alignment |

Override roots when siblings are not peers, e.g. `export LAUNCHFORGE_ROOT=/path/to/LaunchForge`.

# Promotion and dispatch

| Layer | Use when |
|-------|----------|
| Forge MCP | Planning lifecycle stages, signed handoffs, readiness gates |
| OKF promotion | Integrator-reviewed outcomes → `.okf/` concepts with lineage |
| OKF dispatch | Implementation delivery (`scripts/okf-dispatch` when installed) |
| ForgeRelay | Cross-tool agent handoff — parallel to OKF handoffs, not a replacement |

Packet routing: `.okf/references/forge-packet-type-registry.md`.

# Gitignore

Forge workspaces under `.okf/forge/` must stay gitignored. Never commit signing keys, approval receipts, or PII from Forge workspaces.

